dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lee_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9885680195395463, \"rank\": 0.003167798986303392, \"text\": \"David Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lee_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lee_(basketball)\"}, {\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9994018187185906, \"rank\": 0.0005644200176391674, \"text\": \"Maximilian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maximilian_I_of_Mexico\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.999988468800985, \"rank\": 1.1531324592313126e-05, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kayaker Stephenie Chen clocked 1min 55.15sec in her women's canoe sprint K1 500m semi-final in the morning to finish sixth out of eight athletes and earn herself another race.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9998518990105199, \"rank\": 0.00014254123811447995, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fastest two in each of the four semi-finals qualified for Final A, while the others were grouped in Final B (third, fourth) and C (fifth, sixth).\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Final C two hours later at Vaires-sur-Marne, Chen could not hold on to a strong pace in the last 100m and placed seventh out of eight kayakers in 1:56.55 - she finished 23rd out of 40 overall.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9998518990105199, \"rank\": 0.00014254123811447995, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Final A - the medal race - New Zealand's Lisa Carrington won in a new Olympic best of 1:47.36, while Hungary's Tamara Csipes (1:48.44) and Denmark's Emma Jorgensen (1:49.76) took silver and bronze respectively.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9850851800251661, \"rank\": 0.012199705689093709, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Carrington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lisa Carrington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Carrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Carrington\"}, {\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.929435476133601, \"rank\": 0.07592191759352328, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Csipes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tamara Csipes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Csipes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Csipes\"}, {\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5664523334772135, \"rank\": 0.6864279299969602, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999993620105886, \"rank\": 2.4249451743507966e-07, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chen, 32, was particularly pleased with her \\\"fantastic\\\" semi-final, saying: \\\"I am really happy with how my races evolved.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1396, \"end\": 1400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9998518990105199, \"rank\": 0.00014254123811447995, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going into the semis, there were athletes ahead of me on times, and to come on top of others showed I can step up on the biggest stage.\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To qualify for the Final C at the Olympics, placing me in the top 24 is beyond my dreams.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I learnt I can recognise and turn things around when I need to under pressure.\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My performances have solidified my belief of where I stand as an athlete.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was unfortunate to miss out on Tokyo 2020, but I now know I belong.\\\"\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1934, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9441372585969086, \"rank\": 0.05916768594521332, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bill Lee, national coach for sprint kayak, hopes that Chen's performance can inspire the next generation of canoeists.\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Franklin_Lee_III\", \"score\": 0.9617467564028577, \"rank\": 0.03680909327016666, \"text\": \"Bill Lee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Franklin_Lee_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Franklin_Lee_III\"}, {\"begin\": 2002, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"score\": 0.9993552385992802, \"rank\": 0.000645177386382941, \"text\": \"sprint kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_sprint\"}, {\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9998518990105199, \"rank\": 0.00014254123811447995, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"She did really well for her first outing at the Olympics to hold her composure and execute her races according to her plan.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephenie's journey inspires belief that through hard work and dedication, we are able to put Singapore on the world map.\\\"\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.999988468800985, \"rank\": 1.1531324592313126e-05, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chen, however, is undecided about her sporting future and mounting another Olympic campaign, saying: \\\"I have achieved every goal I have set in my career.\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.9998518990105199, \"rank\": 0.00014254123811447995, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Will I reassess and look to build on my strong performances?\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I cannot answer that now... my heart and mind need to be in the right place to go after more performances.\\\"\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the future looks bright for Shannon Tan, as the 20-year-old finished 40th out of 60 golfers in the women's individual competition.\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Shannon\", \"score\": 0.9889318931458841, \"rank\": 0.009171720981440992, \"text\": \"Shannon\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Shannon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Shannon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Le Golf National, Tan finished with a bang as she carded a brilliant eagle on the final hole for a two-over 74 to sign for a seven-over 295 total after four rounds.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her coach Ryan Lumsden said that there are \\\"a lot of positives to take away from this week such as her ball striking\\\".\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2997, \"end\": 3001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9999999997889972, \"rank\": 1.4359171904775594e-10, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}, {\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Burnett_Lumsden\", \"score\": 0.9999835617291454, \"rank\": 1.6437338601740114e-05, \"text\": \"Lumsden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Burnett_Lumsden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Burnett_Lumsden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tan added: \\\"It's always great to end with a good closing hole and it's been a great week for me.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been a pro for only slightly over seven months now, so being able to qualify and play against the best at the Olympics has been such a great experience.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is probably the toughest golf course I have played.\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While there is always room for improvement, I thought I have handled it pretty well here, learnt some new shots and executed the game plan which was set out at the start of the week.\\\"\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the next three weeks, she will return to the Ladies European Tour and play at the Scottish Open, AIG Women's Open, and KPMG Irish Women's Open.\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3658, \"end\": 3678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ladies_European_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9302927506541398e-27, \"text\": \"Ladies European Tour\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ladies_European_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ladies_European_Tour\"}, {\"begin\": 3710, \"end\": 3713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_International_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AIG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_International_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_International_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 3732, \"end\": 3736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KPMG\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KPMG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KPMG\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KPMG\"}, {\"begin\": 3737, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.7877371999068313, \"rank\": 0.25756016613066085, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand's Lydia Ko (71) won gold with a final score of 10-under 278.\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3758, \"end\": 3769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9850851800251661, \"rank\": 0.012199705689093709, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http: